<p><em>What is the largest sum of outcomes possible?</em></p>
<p>In given problem (die toss resulting in 0 or 1 or 2), the maximum possible outcome is 2.<br>
If we toss 4 times, each time maximum possibility is 2, so, the largest sum we could get out of all sequences is $4 \times 2 = 8$</p>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>As can be seen above, for just 1 flip, sum is just the outcome as there is nothing more to add. So X=0 sum 0 occurs 1 time, sum 1 occurs 1 time, and sum 2 occurs 1 time.</p>
<p>$
\text {Let X denote the sum of sequence. Then after 1 toss} \\
X = 0, \ n(X) = 1 \\
X = 1, \ n(X) = 1 \\
X = 2, \ n(X) = 1
$</p>
